goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of fertility vs life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand if there is any relationship between fertility and life expectancy. A positive correlation would indicate that countries with higher fertility rates tend to have lower life expectancies and vice versa.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand the spread of fertility rates across different countries. It can help identify countries with high or low fertility rates.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand the spread of life expectancies across different countries. It can help identify countries with high or low life expectancies.

goals.question: What is the trend of fertility and life expectancy over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of fertility and life_expect over year
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand the trend of fertility and life expectancy over the years. It can help identify if there is any improvement or decline in these factors over time.

goals.question: What is the relationship between normalized fertility and normalized life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of n_fertility vs n_life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand if there is any relationship between normalized fertility and normalized life expectancy. A positive correlation would indicate that countries with higher normalized fertility rates tend to have lower normalized life expectancies and vice versa.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(x='fertility', y='life_expect', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['fertility'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
